Edward,<br>
     What you wrote is fine, but the depth indicated probably can't be covered in a high school history course, where the Vietnam War may or may not be covered at all at the end of the school year.  Providing there aren't too many &quot;snow days&quot; or other things taking up too much time, the Vietnam War may get one or two fifty minute periods.  As for the accuracy of the data; I must admit that most teachers don't ask much about my credentials or sources or check out the resume I make sure they get.  I sometimes wish I would be challenged a bit; so that I know there's some critical thinking being done by the teacher, and hopefully communicated to his students.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


